headline: Sempra shares tank on disappointing Q4 earnings results
summary: Shares of public utility company Sempra Energy (SRE) are tumbling after the company released a weaker-than-expected fourth quarter earnings report and lowered its financial guidance for the year. Watch the video above to hear Market Domination hosts Josh Lipton and Julie Hyman discuss Sempra's performance, the impact of regulatory decisions on utility companies, and how Sempra’s challenges may affect the broader market. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination here. This post was written by Josh Lynch
